result.execSummary:
Dante K Rhodes was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Dante K Rhodes was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

From Atty Weathers requesting to remove the hearing to determine if the defendant was picked up by IOWA Law Enforcement.
Signed by the defendant and Judge Hassin dated 03/27/2014
Warrant for commitment signed by Judge Hassin dated 03/27/2014
Review hearing on April 17, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Dante K Rhodes in court with attorney M Elizabeth Weathers.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant waives right to extradition. Defendant signs forms. Court signs warrant for commitment. State requests bail be revoked so IOWA can pick up the defendant. Court grants request and revokes bail.  Defendant to be returned to IOWA with the proper authorities.  Review hearing scheduled for April 17, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Dante K Rhodes in court, in custody, with attorney M Elizabeth Weathers.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty. Weathers states she will represent the defendant on this case. Atty. Weathers to file a bail motion on the defendant's cases. Warrant for Commitment filed by the State and to remain in file 14CF238 until the next court date. Time limits are tolled on 14CF238. Court will give a date next week on all matters.  Hearing scheduled for March 27, 2014 at 11:00 am.
Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.

Defendant Dante K Rhodes in court, in custody, with attorney Katie Beth Bricco.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  An attorney will be appointed.   NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.
